cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) applications that rely on pre-trained word representations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the training of high-quality word vector representations. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as NLP is a subfield of AI. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word representations are often used in information retrieval tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are often used to train word representations.
